definition.value: A developmental defect characterized by absence or underdevelopment of the calvaria.
Delayed maturation and calcification of the clavicle.
Distance between the sacrum and the ilium bones of the pelvis at the sacroiliac joint is above the upper limit of normal.

label.value: Anti-dachshund family transcription factor 1 antibody positivity
Anti-potassium channel tetramerization domain containing 16 antibody positivity
Anti-regulator of G protein signaling 8 antibody positivity

definition.value: Size (volume) of the head of the humerus above the upper limit of normal.
The concentration of bismuth in the blood is above the upper limit of a guidance value for total blood bismuth concentrations that implies possible injurious effects.
Detection of a level of bismuth in the urine high enough to raise the suspicion of bismuth toxicity, usually greater than 20microgram per deciliter.
Absence of one or more interphalangeal creases of a toe (i.e., of the transverse lines in the skin between the phalanges of the toes).
A benign, well circumscribed neoplasm that arises from the breast.

label.value: Positive mumps virus PCR test in the blood circulation

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of the mumps virus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or reverse transcriptase (RT)-PCR.

label.value: Positive bloodstream tuberculosis-induced T-cell-based interferon-gamma release assay

definition.value: Growth of Neisseria gonorrhoeae in a culture derived from circulating blood.
The presence of antibodies in the blood circulation that react against a component of Mumps virus.
Growth of Vibrio cholerae in a culture derived from a feces sample.

label.value: Positive cutaneous varicella zoster virus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of mucocutaneous varicella zoster virus nucleic acid in the skin by a method such as polymerase chain reaction. The sample is usually obtained by swab from skin or mucous membranes.
Growth of Cryptococcus in a culture derived from a blood sample.

label.value: Positive bloodstream Borrelia miyamotoi nucleic acid test
Positive bloodstream Coxsackievirus nucleic acid pathogen test

definition.value: Detection of nucleic acid of Coxsackievirus in the blood circulation by a method such as polymerase chain reaction (PCR).

Fecal analysis for Cryptosporidium antigen is abnormal. Tests include direct fluorescent-antibody (DFA), which detects intact organisms, and enzyme immunoassays (EIAs), which detect soluble stool antigens.
Bulging in the area of the lower abdomen, just above the thigh and near the groin.

Any abnormal process of ossification of the phalangeal bones, which normally are ossified from the body and proximal extremity. Ossification of the body commences during the eighth week of fetal development. Ossification of the proximal extremity commences in the bones between the third and fourth years.
